["The decision is indicative of vigilance and swiftness of action, which are both necessary for effectively dealing with public health threats," [Ogbonnaya Omenka] told USA Today. "At the same time, there is a risk of the decision feeding into the already existing vaccine hesitancy..."

On the other hand, those who are wary of vaccinations may be reassured by this move, which indicates rapid response to adverse effects no matter how rare. - Mod.LK]

