[While no permanent harm has been identified, it is important that the impact of the vaccine and the disease itself on women's health issues are considered and evaluated. It is known from MMR vaccination, that menstruation is affected. See Nakazono N, Fujimoto S, Wakisaka A, Ishii K, Ichinoe K, Aizawa M. Factors associated with clinical reactions to rubella vaccination in women. Int J Gynaecol Obstet. 1987 Jun; 25(3): 207-16. doi: 10.1016/0020-7292(87)90237-2. PMID: 2886379. - Mod.LK]

